I'll do my best.

583
00:26:50,559 --> 00:26:52,000
And I'll definitely pay back the money.

584
00:26:53,079 --> 00:26:53,960
The mistakes I made—

585
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:55,799
I'll take responsibility.

586
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:57,279
But—

587
00:26:59,799 --> 00:27:00,880
Whether I can go back—

588
00:27:01,680 --> 00:27:02,720
that's up to you.

589
00:27:03,680 --> 00:27:04,799
Of course you have to go back.

590
00:27:06,240 --> 00:27:07,720
You still need to manage the restaurant.

591
00:27:08,240 --> 00:27:10,039
You made such a big mess.

592
00:27:10,279 --> 00:27:11,319
The debt isn't paid off yet.

593
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:12,400
You're not allowed to go anywhere.

594
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:14,559
And that kid Ankar—

595
00:27:14,839 --> 00:27:16,440
He used to be so cheerful.

596
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:18,839
Now, because of this,

597
00:27:19,079 --> 00:27:20,720
he can't even lift his head.

598
00:27:21,200 --> 00:27:22,119
You have to take responsibility.

599
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:25,160
Help him stand tall again.

600
00:27:27,640 --> 00:27:28,559
Sister Aisha,

601
00:27:29,720 --> 00:27:31,119
I'm An Dong's ex-wife.

602
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:33,039
When it comes down to it,

603
00:27:33,759 --> 00:27:35,079
I'm the one who let you all down.

604
00:27:35,759 --> 00:27:36,359
Child,

605
00:27:36,519 --> 00:27:38,799
What does this have to do with you?

606
00:27:40,359 --> 00:27:41,039
Here's the thing—

607
00:27:41,559 --> 00:27:42,920
Actually, a long time ago,

608
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:45,640
I heard her talk about our Hong Shiliu.

609
00:27:46,279 --> 00:27:47,839
Back then, she told me

610
00:27:48,519 --> 00:27:49,920
there's a small restaurant in Urumqi

611
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:52,079
with really amazing food.

612
00:27:52,839 --> 00:27:53,599
It's called Hong Shiliu.

613
00:27:54,279 --> 00:27:55,799
How did you know about me?

614
00:27:57,359 --> 00:27:58,799
My mother is Parida.

615
00:28:00,799 --> 00:28:02,119
Mother Parida.

616
00:28:09,240 --> 00:28:11,240
When I left, you had just been born.

617
00:28:11,599 --> 00:28:13,079
You didn't even have a name yet.

618
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:15,640
I really didn't expect this.

619
00:28:15,799 --> 00:28:16,799
Sister Aisha,

620
00:28:17,680 --> 00:28:19,400
Thanks to your support all these years,

621
00:28:19,839 --> 00:28:21,880
my mother could teach apprentices for free.

622
00:28:22,279 --> 00:28:24,519
She helped more young people learn a craft.

623
00:28:24,839 --> 00:28:27,279
She also passed down her handmade Atlas silk skills.

624
00:28:27,279 --> 00:28:28,319
and kept the tradition alive.

625
00:28:28,839 --> 00:28:30,400
You kindly helped us,

626
00:28:31,400 --> 00:28:32,599
but I dragged you into trouble.

627
00:28:33,880 --> 00:28:35,279
I'm so sorry to you.

628
00:28:35,640 --> 00:28:36,799
No need to apologize.

629
00:28:36,799 --> 00:28:38,559
This isn't your fault.

630
00:28:43,039 --> 00:28:44,319
Now that we've talked it out,

631
00:28:44,759 --> 00:28:46,119
we're even more like family.

632
00:28:46,240 --> 00:28:48,359
Family needs trust.

633
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:49,400
We have to support each other.

634
00:28:49,759 --> 00:28:51,440
And allow mistakes.

635
00:28:56,119 --> 00:28:58,079
I want to visit Mother Parida.

636
00:28:58,440 --> 00:28:59,319
Some things—

637
00:28:59,599 --> 00:29:00,599
what must be faced

638
00:29:01,079 --> 00:29:02,279
still needs to be faced.

639
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:03,319
I'll take you there.

640
00:29:06,559 --> 00:29:07,519
Get in the car.

641
00:29:10,279 --> 00:29:11,079
I'll go too.

642
00:29:11,720 --> 00:29:12,200
Mom.

643
00:29:12,279 --> 00:29:13,559
Maybe you shouldn't go.

644
00:29:14,559 --> 00:29:15,759
In your condition—

645
00:29:15,759 --> 00:29:16,960
if Mom sees you,

646
00:29:18,160 --> 00:29:19,480
she might get upset and fall ill.

647
00:29:38,519 --> 00:29:39,200
Mom.

648
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:41,880
Mom.

649
00:29:44,279 --> 00:29:44,960
Look,

650
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:46,799
who's here.

651
00:29:47,519 --> 00:29:48,680
Guess who I brought.

652
00:29:49,480 --> 00:29:50,359
Who?

653
00:30:00,759 --> 00:30:01,880
Aisha.

654
00:30:05,440 --> 00:30:07,319
My stubborn girl—

655
00:30:12,440 --> 00:30:15,039
finally decided to come back.

656
00:30:31,880 --> 00:30:32,680
Child,

657
00:30:33,559 --> 00:30:36,119
you've had a hard time out there alone.

658
00:30:45,200 --> 00:30:45,799
Mom.

659
00:30:50,039 --> 00:30:51,039
Mother Parida.

660
00:30:51,279 --> 00:30:52,680
This is my son, Ming Liang.

661
00:30:53,400 --> 00:30:54,279
Ming Liang.

662
00:30:54,920 --> 00:30:55,759
Grandma Parida.

663
00:30:58,119 --> 00:30:59,000
Child,

664
00:31:02,319 --> 00:31:03,799
my grandson.

665
00:31:13,319 --> 00:31:14,079
You go back first.

666
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:16,799
I'll stay with my mom and Grandma Parida for two more days.

667
00:31:19,839 --> 00:31:20,240
Alright.

668
00:31:22,039 --> 00:31:22,720
Um...

669
00:31:23,440 --> 00:31:24,519
No need to see me off.

670
00:31:26,680 --> 00:31:27,640
The car will be here soon.

671
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:32,839
About the restaurant—

672
00:31:34,079 --> 00:31:34,680
I'll do my best.

673
00:31:35,799 --> 00:31:36,599
You and Aisha—

674
00:31:37,359 --> 00:31:38,079
don't worry either.

675
00:31:46,119 --> 00:31:47,119
Keep this IOU with you.

676
00:31:57,079 --> 00:31:58,319
If taking this piece of paper

677
00:31:58,720 --> 00:32:00,039
can make you feel a bit better,

678
00:32:01,960 --> 00:32:02,799
then I'll accept it.

679
00:32:03,279 --> 00:32:03,880
But

680
00:32:04,960 --> 00:32:06,119
money can be repaid,

681
00:32:08,039 --> 00:32:09,599
but if you hurt someone's heart again,

682
00:32:11,519 --> 00:32:12,720
it can't be fixed.

683
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:16,759
When I go back,

684
00:32:18,279 --> 00:32:19,920
I'll apologize to each of them.

685
00:32:21,359 --> 00:32:22,279
Especially to Ankar.

686
00:32:23,279 --> 00:32:24,359
Whether he accepts you

687
00:32:26,559 --> 00:32:27,599
is up to you.

688
00:32:30,599 --> 00:32:31,440
You two talk first.

689
00:32:31,599 --> 00:32:32,480
I'll go check on my mom.

690
00:32:40,640 --> 00:32:42,680
How is Aisha's illness?

691
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:43,640
Is it serious?

692
00:32:47,599 --> 00:32:48,319
Brain tumor.

693
00:32:50,079 --> 00:32:51,119
It's pressing on her optic nerve.

694
00:32:52,319 --> 00:32:53,319
She might lose her sight.

695
00:32:55,519 --> 00:32:56,799
Don't tell Mom about this.

696
00:33:00,039 --> 00:33:01,279
Don't tell Parida either.

697
00:33:02,599 --> 00:33:03,359
Aisha

698
00:33:05,279 --> 00:33:06,319
doesn't want others to worry.

699
00:33:06,799 --> 00:33:08,079
You know she's this sick,

700
00:33:08,079 --> 00:33:09,200
yet you still treat her this way.

701
00:33:09,880 --> 00:33:11,279
What can I even say to you?

702
00:33:17,759 --> 00:33:19,680
This is the card you gave me before.

703
00:33:21,039 --> 00:33:22,440
There's a bit of interest left.

704
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:25,279
Not much, though.

705
00:33:25,960 --> 00:33:26,920
Just take it for now.

706
00:33:38,319 --> 00:33:40,000
The moment you jumped into the lake,

707
00:33:41,319 --> 00:33:43,039
the old An Dong in my heart

708
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:44,000
was already gone.

709
00:33:47,119 --> 00:33:48,880
Let the past stay in the past.

710
00:33:50,079 --> 00:33:51,039
Live well from now on.

711
00:33:52,039 --> 00:33:53,559
I'll live my own life, too.

712
00:33:56,240 --> 00:33:56,680
Okay.

713
00:33:59,279 --> 00:34:00,200
I will.

714
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:03,640
I thought you'd refuse like before.

715
00:34:04,079 --> 00:34:05,039
Not willing to accept it.

716
00:34:09,199 --> 00:34:10,079
Back then,

717
00:34:11,440 --> 00:34:13,679
I thought I could do everything.

718
00:34:14,800 --> 00:34:15,480
Never asked for help.

719
00:34:16,239 --> 00:34:17,039
Never owed anyone.

720
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:18,840
Looking back now,

721
00:34:19,440 --> 00:34:20,280
I was too arrogant.

722
00:34:23,079 --> 00:34:23,960
Living in this world,

723
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:26,000
how could anyone not need help?

724
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:28,599
Admitting you need help

725
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:30,000
is also a kind of courage.

726
00:34:30,920 --> 00:34:31,480
That's right.

727
00:34:34,239 --> 00:34:34,760
I'm leaving.

728
00:34:46,960 --> 00:34:48,360
So you called me

729
00:34:48,599 --> 00:34:50,159
just to ask if I got the card?

730
00:34:51,400 --> 00:34:52,159
Not really.

731
00:34:53,159 --> 00:34:55,039
I just wanted to tell you

732
00:34:55,519 --> 00:34:56,559
everything's been sorted out.

733
00:34:56,880 --> 00:34:57,519
Don't worry.

734
00:34:57,679 --> 00:34:58,679
Alright, I know.

735
00:34:59,800 --> 00:35:00,679
Still mad?

736
00:35:01,800 --> 00:35:03,199
Mom and I still have things to do here.

737
00:35:04,199 --> 00:35:05,480
It'll be a few days before we return.

738
00:35:06,599 --> 00:35:07,639
Take good care of yourself.

739
00:35:09,119 --> 00:35:10,920
Don't get so busy you forget yourself.

740
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:12,440
Some things

741
00:35:13,960 --> 00:35:15,519
I'll tell you in person when I'm back.

742
00:35:15,800 --> 00:35:17,239
Okay, I know. I'm hanging up.

743
00:35:21,480 --> 00:35:23,000
The wind and sand in Hotan are strong.

744
00:35:23,599 --> 00:35:25,320
Remember to look after Aisha.

745
00:35:26,079 --> 00:35:27,000
And yourself, too.

746
00:35:43,280 --> 00:35:43,960
Nana,

747
00:35:44,400 --> 00:35:45,039
his personality—

748
00:35:45,039 --> 00:35:46,079
you know how he is.

749
00:35:46,320 --> 00:35:47,199
Making him take your money

750
00:35:47,199 --> 00:35:48,719
is like asking for his life.

751
00:35:49,039 --> 00:35:50,679
But he can't be like this forever.

752
00:35:51,320 --> 00:35:53,239
If he wants to keep going,

753
00:35:53,519 --> 00:35:55,239
he has to get past that hurdle.

754
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:03,559
Atlas silk here is especially famous.

755
00:36:04,239 --> 00:36:05,199
Next time we come,

756
00:36:05,199 --> 00:36:06,920
we must find a chance to see it well.

757
00:37:03,599 --> 00:37:04,559
That's a beautiful drawing.

758
00:37:05,639 --> 00:37:06,800
Is she your girlfriend?

759
00:37:08,559 --> 00:37:09,599
Yes, Hatiman.

760
00:37:12,079 --> 00:37:13,119
This pattern

761
00:37:13,800 --> 00:37:15,679
isn't the traditional Atlas silk.

762
00:37:17,079 --> 00:37:18,920
I just looked at these designs

763
00:37:18,920 --> 00:37:19,960
and pieced them together.

764
00:37:21,239 --> 00:37:21,960
I think this way

765
00:37:22,039 --> 00:37:23,280
the colors match better.

766
00:37:24,039 --> 00:37:25,480
It suits her temperament more.

767
00:37:30,599 --> 00:37:32,199
No wonder you're an artist.

768
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:34,360
I tried before, too,

769
00:37:34,360 --> 00:37:35,599
wanted to change the patterns.

770
00:37:36,199 --> 00:37:37,480
But when I drew them myself,

771
00:37:37,480 --> 00:37:38,840
they always felt a bit off.

772
00:37:41,159 --> 00:37:41,920
It's really beautiful.

773
00:37:43,400 --> 00:37:44,079
Ming Liang,

774
00:37:44,599 --> 00:37:46,280
why not use this pattern

775
00:37:46,360 --> 00:37:47,360
to weave a scarf

776
00:37:48,239 --> 00:37:49,320
for your girlfriend?

777
00:37:50,920 --> 00:37:51,760
My father

778
00:37:51,800 --> 00:37:53,840
used to make Atlas silk too.

779
00:37:54,480 --> 00:37:56,719
The token he gave my mother

780
00:37:56,719 --> 00:37:59,159
was an Atlas silk scarf.

781
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:00,719
My mom said

782
00:38:01,199 --> 00:38:03,679
it was the most beautiful Atlas silk she'd seen.

783
00:38:04,079 --> 00:38:05,280
Because it had Dad's love.

784
00:38:08,800 --> 00:38:10,440
Make one just for her—

785
00:38:10,440 --> 00:38:12,079
an Atlas silk scarf.

786
00:38:12,239 --> 00:38:13,599
She'll definitely love it.

787
00:38:16,199 --> 00:38:17,840
I should make her a scarf.

788
00:38:20,119 --> 00:38:21,000
As an apology.

789
00:38:22,320 --> 00:38:23,239
Did you mess up?

790
00:38:27,440 --> 00:38:28,920
I did what I thought was good for her,

791
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:31,960
but ended up hurting her.

792
00:38:35,800 --> 00:38:37,239
Is it about money?

793
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:43,199
You don't want her to share the burden?

794
00:38:49,280 --> 00:38:49,800
Ming Liang,

795
00:38:51,800 --> 00:38:52,880
when a girl

796
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:54,599
is willing to stay with you

797
00:38:54,599 --> 00:38:55,920
through your hardest times,

798
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:57,400
that's your good fortune.

799
00:38:58,159 --> 00:38:59,880
Don't feel embarrassed about it.

800
00:39:01,119 --> 00:39:02,840
Keep this kindness in your heart.

801
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:04,400
Respond in the way she hopes.

802
00:39:04,480 --> 00:39:05,880
Answer her love for you.

803
00:39:07,360 --> 00:39:09,400
That's the greatest respect for her.

804
00:39:14,679 --> 00:39:15,719
Don't be like An Dong,

805
00:39:17,079 --> 00:39:20,199
doing things his way for others.

806
00:39:21,440 --> 00:39:21,960
Sis,

807
00:39:22,400 --> 00:39:23,199
your phone.

808
00:39:27,199 --> 00:39:27,559
Hello?

809
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:28,280
Aizizi?

810
00:39:28,800 --> 00:39:29,400
What's wrong?

811
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:31,559
Secretary Xu isn't here.

812
00:39:32,800 --> 00:39:34,000
The TV's broken again.

813
00:39:35,599 --> 00:39:36,880
I can't fix it either.

814
00:39:37,880 --> 00:39:38,800
I'll go take a look.

815
00:39:39,599 --> 00:39:40,800
Calm Grandma Aman down

816
00:39:41,360 --> 00:39:43,400
so she doesn't go out looking for people.

817
00:39:44,119 --> 00:39:44,559
Alright.

818
00:39:45,239 --> 00:39:45,760
Hatiman,

819
00:39:45,960 --> 00:39:47,000
I'll go with you.

820
00:39:47,320 --> 00:39:48,440
See if I can help.

821
00:39:49,559 --> 00:39:49,920
Okay.

822
00:40:03,840 --> 00:40:04,679
Secretary Xu

823
00:40:05,840 --> 00:40:06,519
Take a break.

824
00:40:06,639 --> 00:40:07,639
Have some tea.

825
00:40:07,760 --> 00:40:08,400
Grandma

826
00:40:09,119 --> 00:40:10,280
He's not Secretary Xu.

827
00:40:10,440 --> 00:40:10,960
What?

828
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:12,920
He's not Secretary Xu.

829
00:40:13,039 --> 00:40:13,880
He's my relative.

830
00:40:13,880 --> 00:40:15,000
His name is Ming Liang.

831
00:40:15,119 --> 00:40:16,880
Secretary Xu can't find a partner.

832
00:40:18,320 --> 00:40:19,320
It's getting more confusing.

833
00:40:19,800 --> 00:40:20,960
Grandma is getting old.

834
00:40:21,239 --> 00:40:22,719
Her hearing and sight aren't good.

835
00:40:23,320 --> 00:40:25,280
She mistook you for Secretary Xu.

836
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:27,920
Thank you.

837
00:40:31,559 --> 00:40:32,320
How much longer?

838
00:40:33,639 --> 00:40:34,119
It's done.

839
00:40:37,760 --> 00:40:38,639
Aman

840
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:39,719
Aman

841
00:40:39,800 --> 00:40:41,559
Let's play house.

842
00:40:43,159 --> 00:40:44,360
What am I playing today?

843
00:40:45,079 --> 00:40:45,920
I'm the mom.

844
00:40:45,960 --> 00:40:47,280
You play the dad.

845
00:40:47,920 --> 00:40:49,039
I don't want to be the dad.

846
00:40:49,440 --> 00:40:51,440
But only the dad is left.

847
00:40:51,519 --> 00:40:52,599
Then I'm not playing.

848
00:40:53,920 --> 00:40:54,960
Me neither.

849
00:40:54,960 --> 00:40:56,239
Who wants to play with you?

850
00:40:59,639 --> 00:41:00,280
I'll go call.

851
00:41:01,199 --> 00:41:02,679
Aman, Aman

852
00:41:03,280 --> 00:41:04,000
Aman

853
00:41:06,119 --> 00:41:06,880
Let's go.

854
00:41:11,519 --> 00:41:14,320
Secretary Xu really has a lot to handle.

855
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:16,119
That's for sure.

856
00:41:16,719 --> 00:41:18,519
Aman's grandma's son and daughter-in-law

857
00:41:18,519 --> 00:41:19,760
are all working out of town.

858
00:41:20,039 --> 00:41:21,760
Only the old and the young are left at home.

859
00:41:22,239 --> 00:41:25,000
Secretary Xu comes here every few days.

860
00:41:25,599 --> 00:41:26,280
Last time

861
00:41:26,320 --> 00:41:28,199
Good thing he found the fridge broken.

862
00:41:28,400 --> 00:41:30,679
The leftovers inside had gone bad.

863
00:41:31,480 --> 00:41:32,559
He brought Aizezi

864
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:34,360
and cleaned up all afternoon.

865
00:41:34,920 --> 00:41:35,559
Now

866
00:41:35,599 --> 00:41:38,199
even Aman's homework

867
00:41:38,280 --> 00:41:40,440
is tutored by Secretary Xu himself.

868
00:41:41,239 --> 00:41:42,079
You can tell

869
00:41:42,920 --> 00:41:44,440
Grandma really likes Secretary Xu.

870
00:41:44,840 --> 00:41:45,360
Yes.

871
00:41:46,159 --> 00:41:47,119
This Secretary Xu

872
00:41:47,199 --> 00:41:48,000
is quite interesting.

